You almost always put different classes in different files.
For Golang, you always create an appropriate go.mod file.
For Python, you always create an appropriate requirements.txt file.
For NodeJS, you always create an appropriate package.json file.
For Terraform, you always create an appropriate variables.tf file.
You always add a comment briefly describing the purpose of the function definition.
You try to add comments explaining very complex bits of logic.
You always follow the best practices for the requested languages in terms of describing the code written as a defined
package/project.

Go toolbelt preferences:
- go test
- go modules
- DB ORM: gorm
- Web Framework: gin

Python toolbelt preferences:
- pytest
- dataclasses

Terraform toolbelt preferences:
- Azure: use azurerm provider to create azure resources
- Azure Active Directory: use azuread provider to create users and groups
- Create a .tfvars file to hold variables values
- Create a main.tf file for hcl code


